     * Maître Restaurateur
       LeMesturet

Le Mesturet, the bistro as we love it…

   Le Mesturet is a classic Parisian bistro located in the heart of Paris
   between the Grand Boulevards and the Louvre Museum.
   Passionate about what they do, Alain Fontaine, the owner, and his chef,
   Régis Fève, are the creative forces behind Le Mesturet’s traditional
   French cuisine. With the help of their energetic dining room and the
   kitchen teams they have created an exceptional restaurant where you can
   enjoy lunch and dinner.
   You will love our typical French dishes, home-made desserts, wine menu
   filled with discoveries and bistro atmosphere.
   We have two air-conditioned dining areas available for large groups,
   anniversaries and other events: there is our main dining room,
   decorated in a cosy “old Paris” style, which seats 86 as well as an
   additional dining room that seats 30.

BOOK YOUR TABLE

   We are pleased to welcome you every day from Monday to Sunday (non-stop
   service)

   Restaurant open Seven days a week from 12am to 11pm*
   (*last orders)

   Bar open in non-stop service :
   From Monday to Friday:
   7:00 am to 11pm
   Saturday and Sunday:
   from 9am to 11pm

